\f0\fs32 \cf0 \ul \ulc0 SLIDE 7a:
\f1\fs24 \ulnone \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl360
\ls15\ilvl0
\f0\fs32 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}The final step in our description transformation process is to create Dublin Core to feed into Islandora as metadata for our digital content\
{\listtext	\'95	}We can either convert MARCXML or EAD into Dublin Core using an XSLT\
{\listtext	\'95	}Or we can feed MARCXML directly into Islandora using Islandora\'92s native MARCXML convertor\
{\listtext	\'95	}Either way, we have a relatively simple way of generating Dublin Core from our previous work describing the material\
{\listtext	\'95	}This is where diverting resources towards archival description and cataloguing practices can pay dividends towards a sustainable workflow for digital content creation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360
\cf0  
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li960\sl360

\f0\fs32 \cf0 \ul \ulc0 SLIDE 7b:
\f1\fs24 \ulnone \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl360
\ls16\ilvl0
\f0\fs32 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}As for the creation of the digital objects themselves, we are lucky to have plenty of options here at UofT\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl360
\ls17\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Setting up training modules is a big part of making digitization sustainable for the library - it helps us ensure that material is digitized consistently and supports knowledge transference between the individuals who do digitization work\
{\listtext	\'95	}We can also use open source software like GIMP, mogrify, and SublimeText so that our budget is dedicated towards human resources rather than software licenses\
{\listtext	\'95	}We\'92ve had great success at UTSC employing undergraduate students through the work-study program to complete digitization work - this is a very low cost option for us as the university pays 80% of their salary\
{\listtext	\'95	}We also have the Internet Archive option for works that are fully out of US copyright, which again is relatively inexpensive, I think ten cents per page, and can run off books quite quickly\
{\listtext	\'95	}For a more expanded project, we\'92re lucky enough to have the iSchool next door so that we can act as a placement for graduate students in LIS\
{\listtext	\'95	}The actual ingest into Islandora is very simple; we just match up our Dublin Core XML files and our digitized objects, zip them together, and ingest as a batch into the system\
\pard\pardeftab720

